.SH NAME
PannerNode.distanceModel \- PannerNode: distanceModel property
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[CR]distanceModel\f[R] property of the \f[CR]PannerNode\f[R]
interface is an enumerated value determining which algorithm to use to
reduce the volume of the audio source as it moves away from the
listener.
.PP
The possible values are:
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]linear\f[R]: A \f[I]linear distance model\f[R] calculating the
gain induced by the distance according to:
\f[CR]1 \- rolloffFactor * (distance \- refDistance) / (maxDistance \- refDistance)\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]inverse\f[R]: An \f[I]inverse distance model\f[R] calculating the
gain induced by the distance according to:
\f[CR]refDistance / (refDistance + rolloffFactor * (Math.max(distance, refDistance) \- refDistance))\f[R]
.IP \[bu] 2
\f[CR]exponential\f[R]: An \f[I]exponential distance model\f[R]
calculating the gain induced by the distance according to:
\f[CR]pow((Math.max(distance, refDistance) / refDistance, \-rolloffFactor)\f[R].
.PP
\f[CR]inverse\f[R] is the default value of \f[CR]distanceModel\f[R].
.SH VALUE
An enum \[em] see \c
.UR https://webaudio.github.io/web-audio-api/#idl-def-DistanceModelType
\f[CR]DistanceModelType\f[R]
.UE \c
\&.
